title: Hunterdon Central volleyball earns top seed in tourney
text:
Hunterdon Central volleyball earns top seed in tourney Lauren Knego , @laurenknego 8:59 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 Volleyball 1 CONNECT 5 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The Hunterdon Central High School girls volleyball team earned the top seed in the Hunterdon/Warren/Sussex Tournament. 
The Red Devils (17-1) fell to North Hunterdon in last season's final in straight sets, 25-19, 25-19. North Hunterdon (8-7) earned the No. 2 seed in the tournament, which begins Thursday with a qualifying round. 
The quarterfinals are set for Friday at the site of the higher seed. The semifinals and final will be contested on Saturday at Hackettstown starting at 12:30 p.m. The final will follow the semifinals. 
Here is the bracket: 
9-Sparta at 8-Vernon, winner at 1-Hunterdon Central; 5-Hackettstown at 4-Delaware Valley; 6-Warren Hills at 3-Delaware Valley; 7-Pope John at 2-North Hunterdon. Read or Share this story: http://mycj.co/1RWuA7f TOP VIDEOS
